{"title":"7 Christmas Breakfast Ideas From The Pioneer Woman","slug":"7-christmas-breakfast-ideas-from-the-pioneer-woman","date":"2020-12-18T18:37:01","author":"Chino Valley Ranchers","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Christmas is a time for friends, family and good food. Whether you’ve got a Christmas morning breakfast tradition, or you’re ready to make some new ones, here are a few recipes from the Pioneer Woman to get you started.</span></p>\n<p><!--more--><b>1. Cinnamon Rolls</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No, don’t buy cinnamon rolls at the grocery store! These home-baked rolls will get everyone coming back for seconds!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the recipe you’ll need whole milk, vegetable oil, sugar, dry yeast, all-purpose four, baking powder, salt, melted butter, sugar and cinnamon. For the frosting, you’ll need powdered sugar, maple flavoring, milk, melted butter, salt and brewed coffee.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the full </span><a href=\"https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/food-cooking/recipes/a11914/cinammon-rolls/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>2. Eggs Benedict Strata</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can prep this breakfast casserole the night before, so you can just pop it into the oven first thing Christmas morning.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this recipe you’ll need English muffins, eggs, whole milk, half-and-half, salt, black pepper, olive oil, Canadian bacon, baby spinach, salted butter and grated white cheddar cheese. Create your Hollandiase sauce with salted butter, salt, black pepper, lemon, egg yolks, and some hot sauce.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the full </span><a href=\"https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/food-cooking/recipes/a34657722/eggs-benedict-strata-recipe/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>3. Lemon-Poppy Seed Waffles</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Surprise your family with a new take on waffles with lemon-poppy seed waffles from the Pioneer Woman.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You’ll need all-purpose flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, poppy seeds, lemons, salt, milk, eggs, vanilla extract, salted butter, cooking spray and powdered sugar. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the full </span><a href=\"https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/food-cooking/recipes/a33407811/lemon-poppy-seed-waffles-recipe/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>4. Cream Cheese Danishes</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One thing you can’t have too much of during the holidays is dessert. So add cream cheese danishes to your list of Christmas desserts.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this homemade recipe you’ll need cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla extract, almond extract, egg, water, fine sea salt, and one package of puff pastry sheets.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the full </span><a href=\"https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/food-cooking/recipes/a105016/cream-cheese-danish/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>5. Roasted Squash and Bacon Hash</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add a bit of veggies and protein to your breakfast to keep your kids from bouncing off the walls with too much sugar early on in the day.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this roasted squash and bacon hash dish you’ll need acorn squash, red potatoes, yellow onion, baby bella mushrooms, salt, pepper, bacon and butter.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the full </span><a href=\"https://www.thepioneerwoman.com/food-cooking/recipes/a100503/roasted-squash-and-bacon-hash/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n"}